translated: Dufwenberg, Gustav Wilhelm Josef, engineer, from Motala, born on December 22nd, 1879 in Stockholm. Married in 1909 to Ester Ingeborg Claesson. Children: Erik, born in 1910, Stina in 1912, and Karin in 1926. Studied at Borås Technical High School. Worked as an assistant engineer for Västra Central Railway from 1904 to 1906, as divisional engineer for Nora-Bergslags Railway in 1907, the same position at Rydö Hylte Railway in 1908, at Dalby-Bjärsjölagårds Railway building from 1909 to 1912, and at Sävsjöström-Nässjö Railway building from 1913 to 1914. Owned his own road and bridge building company from 1915 to 1918, and became managing director of Josef Dufwenberg A-B in Motala from 1919. He was a member of the board of directors for Josef Dufwenberg A-B since 1919, the West Östergötland Tourist Traffic Association since 1936, Motala's street, health, tennis hall, and Motala Savings Bank's Jubilee Fund. He was also a member of the board of directors for the local primary school and for the municipality's unemployment commission in Motala. An awarded member of the Odd Fellow Lodge #105, Ankaret.
